parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause electrical fires, which can result in serious damage to the vehicle and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: The ignition switch feels hot
the ignition switch sticks or locks up
the vehicle stalls or won't start
the dashboard lights and radio remain on while the engine is off
the starter motor engages when the clutch is depressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause electrical fires, which can result in serious damage to the vehicle and potential harm to occupants. It can also lead to a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Smoke emerges from the dashboard or defroster vents
the wiring harness under the hood or instrument panel is damaged or burning
the fuse blows frequently
the vehicle's electrical system shuts down
the third brake light
rear window defroster
or hatch light malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness can cause electrical fires, which can result in serious damage to the vehicle and potential harm to occupants. It can also lead to a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The wiring harness is damaged or burning
the insulation is cut or damaged during assembly
bare wires or cut wires are shorting to the chassis ground
the third brake light
rear window defroster
or hatch light malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system leaks and failures can cause fuel to leak onto the ground, creating a fire hazard, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries. Additionally, fuel leaks can also cause damage to the vehicle's electrical system and other components.
symptoms: Fuel smell inside the vehicle
fuel leaks from the top of the gas tank
fuel puddles on the ground
fuel leaks from the fuel tank area
fuel gauge not working
fuel pump failure
cracks in the fuel tank or fuel pump sending unit.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracks and leaks in the fuel tank can cause fuel to leak onto the ground, creating a fire hazard, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the top of the gas tank
fuel puddles on the ground
fuel leaks from the fuel tank area
cracks in the fuel tank or fuel pump sending unit.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump Failure and Sending Unit Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel pump failure and sending unit issues can cause fuel leaks, fuel pump failure, and electrical system damage, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel pump failure
fuel leaks from the fuel tank area
cracks in the fuel pump sending unit
fuel gauge not working.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seatbelt retractor can cause the seatbelt to malfunction, leading to a loss of protection in the event of an accident, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seatbelt does not retract properly
the seatbelt gets stuck or jammed
the seatbelt does not lock up in an emergency
the seatbelt cable breaks or hangs out of the retractor
the seatbelt does not work properly
the seatbelt is inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt to restrain the occupant in an accident can cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seatbelt fails to restrain the occupant
the seatbelt does not hold up in an accident
the seatbelt breaks or malfunctions
the occupant is not properly restrained.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, increased risk of accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly

even when the driver takes their foot off the accelerator pedal; vehicle idle speed remains high; throttle pedal sticks or feels stuck; vehicle surges or accelerates on its own; difficulty controlling the vehicle due to unwarranted acceleration.
